THORAX AND ABDOMEN. Body length 4.30–5.30 mm (see
Table. 1
), elongate (
Fig. 7
). Abdominal segments I– V almost equal in length, slightly larger than abdominal segment VI and VII (
Fig. 7
). Spiracles on abdomen in median parts of segments (abdominal seg. I–VIII).

MORPHOLOGY (
Figs. 11–15
). Body length 2.75–4.35 mm ; widest part 1.55–2.20 mm (see
Table. 2
). Body rather elongated and slender. Rostrum long, approximately 6 times as long as wide, reaching mesocoxae. Pronotum 2.2 times as wide as long.

CHAETOTAXY (
Figs. 11–15
). Setae distinct, short, unequal in length, light brown or brown, almost as thornlike. Vs and os slightly longer than other setae of head and rostrum (
Fig. 12
). Ds slightly shorter than other setae on pronotum (
Fig. 14
). Setae on abdominal segments I–VIII placed posteromedially and posterolaterally; all abdominal setae located on thorn-like protuberances, short, curved. Pseudocerci short, conical.
